## Notes, correctness checks, and small critiques

- **Design alignment.** Your base stylesheet already defines semantic tokens for backgrounds, text, primary/CTA colors, outlines, and light/dark toggles. The form styles consume only those tokens so the section visually integrates with the rest of the site and automatically respects the theme switcher. fileciteturn0file2  
- **Placement.** This is built to replace the existing `#contact` block in your HTML, which is presently just a stub. The hero CTA “Contact Form” already links to `#contact`, so all in‑site navigation keeps working. fileciteturn0file1
- **Accessibility.**  
  - Semantic fieldsets/legends, labels, and radio groups are used.  
  - Visible focus is preserved via your global `:focus-visible` rule and reinforced on inputs. fileciteturn0file2  
  - Status messages are announced via `aria-live`.  
- **Validation.** Required fields are `email`, `given_name`, `message`. Phone is optional but pattern‑checked when present.  
- **Spam hardening.** A hidden “website” honeypot field quietly blocks simple bots; Formspree will receive it, but you can filter on their side if needed.  
- **Security/PII.** Posting a raw email on the page invites scraping. If spam becomes an issue, obfuscate the address or rely on WhatsApp + the form instead.  
- **Content tweaks.** Replace the email string in the left card if you prefer a branded mailbox (e.g., `hello@sgmathtuition.com`).  

